# Nelson Schnebelen — Global Claude Code Memory

I run **Dineline**, a restaurant marketing agency. I build campaign-matched landing pages, run paid ad campaigns, and ship sites fast for restaurant clients.

This file is auto-injected into every Claude Code session on this machine. It is the standing brief.

## House design philosophy (apply to every web/UI project)

**Aim for A-tier minimum. S-tier on flagships.** No Squarespace energy, no generic Tailwind-template look.

- Self-contained single-file HTML where possible — drag-and-drop deployability matters
- Inline GSAP, Lenis, ScrollTrigger from `%USERPROFILE%\.claude\toolkit\` — do not link to CDNs
- Aceternity / Magic UI patterns as the component vocabulary (see `toolkit\aceternity-vocabulary.md`)
- Real photography over stock — generate via Replicate (`toolkit\replicate-setup.md`) when needed
- Typography: serif display + sans body, max 2 typefaces per page
- Motion choreography via GSAP timelines, not CSS keyframes
- Smooth scroll via Lenis on every page

## Phase roadmap for any landing page

1. **Phase 1 — A-tier:** Replicate imagery + GSAP/Lenis + Aceternity patterns
2. **Phase 2 — cinematic:** Scroll-orchestrated sequences with ScrollTrigger pin/scrub
3. **Phase 3 — flagship:** Spline 3D embed + custom shaders

