## Restaurant page deploy workflow

- Each restaurant gets its own GitHub repo under `nelsonschnebelen/<restaurant-slug>`
- Repos are connected to Netlify with auto-deploy from `main`
- I edit `index.html` → `git commit` → `git push` → live in ~10 seconds
- No drag-and-drop, no zips

## Stack defaults

- HTML/CSS/JS — single file, self-contained
- React/Next.js + shadcn/ui — when the project demands components (rare; only for multi-page sites)
- Tailwind — for prototyping only; production uses hand-written CSS variables

## What I'm NOT looking for
- Boilerplate explanations of what code does
- Apologetic prose ("I hope this helps", "let me know if…")
- Suggesting alternatives when I've already picked an approach
- Generic stock-photo placeholders
